# Trivy ignore file — https://trivy.dev/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
# Consumed automatically by the `trivy-fs` job in .github/workflows/security.yaml
# (scan-ref is the repo root). Every entry must be justified below.

# DS-0002 (HIGH): "Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with a non-root user".
# Accepted for THIS application Dockerfile — the fix belongs in the base image, not here.
# The base image (jaylordibe/laravel-php) runs `supervisord -> nginx`, and nginx must bind
# port 80 (a privileged port) so Elastic Beanstalk can route traffic to the container. The
# nginx master process therefore starts as root to bind :80 and then drops its worker
# processes to the unprivileged `www-data` user via the `user` directive — the standard,
# secure nginx model. Adding `USER www-data` to this Dockerfile would stop nginx binding
# :80 and break the deployment. Proper hardening (non-privileged port + explicit drop) is
# tracked in the base image jaylordibe/laravel-php; remove this ignore once that lands.
DS-0002
